FBIS4-10655 "drlat073_t_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 Venezuela Senate Approves Special Powers for President Senate Approves Special Powers for President PA1404192494 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1853 GMT 14 Apr 94 PA1404192494 Hamburg DPA Spanish BFN [Text] Caracas, 14 Apr (DPA)--The Venezuelan Senate today approved the so-called Special Powers Act, granting special powers to President Rafael Caldera to decree economic and financial measures. This law will give Caldera special powers to legislate, a function that basically belongs to the Congress. The Special Powers Act was proposed to implement legislative initiatives pertaining to income tax, general sales and excise taxes, tax reform, bank debit tax, the Stamp Tax Law, and the Concessions Law.
